episodes.title: A Fat Bald White Man
episodes.plot: Five, fresh competitors go head-to-head as the gloriously bonkers show returns for an expanded fourth series. They paint a model they can't see, fell a load of rubber ducks and beautifully destroy a cake.

episodes.title: Look at Me
episodes.plot: The participants present prizes they have won. Other tasks include long distance painting, intense staring and putting an egg in an eggcup. Joe Lycett has a personal task - to smile every 30 seconds.

episodes.title: Hollowing Out a Baguette
episodes.plot: Taskmaster Greg Davies tries to spot the five camouflaged comedians before they try to herd dogs and chickens. They also have to re-home a fish and create a trailer for Taskmaster: The Movie.

episodes.title: Friendship Is Truth
episodes.plot: Which guest can perform the best moves on a pommel horse and other ridiculous tasks.

episodes.title: Meat
episodes.plot: The five witless guests attempt to score points by completing wacky tasks, but can they all cooperate for the team task?

episodes.title: Spatchcock It
episodes.plot: The feckless five attempt to go biblical and pass the camel through the eye of a needle, along with other pointless and hilarious tasks.

episodes.title: No Stars for Naughty Boys
episodes.plot: The guests have to come up with a special handshake and other wacky challenges.

episodes.title: Tony Three Pies
episodes.plot: Season finale in which the feckless five have to create the most exotic sandwich and other ridiculous tasks.
